-- ADR to Stop Fiumicino Plan as Rate Increase Blocked: Messaggero
-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 2012-12-18T08:26:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-18/adr-to-stop-fiumicino-plan-as-rate-increase-blocked-messaggero.html
Benetton-controlled ADR has frozen
its 1.8 billion-euro investment plan for Rome’s Fiumicino
airport because the government hasn’t acted on a planned rate
increase, newspaper Il Messaggero reported without citing
anyone.
* Tariff increase being blocked by inaction of  Finance Ministry :
Messaggero
* Prime Minister Mario Monti set to resign this week, meaning no
action on the airport rates until a new government is in place
* NOTE: Sintonia Urges Italy to Approve Rome Airport Concession
